cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI

The paper discusses the impact of Open Access on citation rates, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the dissemination and access of digital information, including Open Access. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as it deals with the retrieval and analysis of information, including citation analysis. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as it deals with the social impact of technology, including Open Access. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible categories as they may involve citation analysis and Open Access in certain contexts.
